inn1.comm: swing first up, from a good length, angled in from wide of the crease, but starting outside off, and left alone
pitched further up, closer to off to, Simmons is back and across to block
shuffles across a long way, leans and turns one angled in on a length in front of square leg
full at 123 kph on off, Simmons leans forward to push it away
pitched up for the drive outside off at 124 kph, moving away, Simmons has a look and shoulders arms
this one does not swing away, comes in with the angle just around off stump, Simmons is shuffling across and turns it to fine leg
away swing, most of it after it has passed the batsman far outside off stump
that was a lot closer to off stump, straightening on a good length, Simmons leaves again
beaten, has a flail after shuffling across to a wide one, it moves further away from back of a length
on the pads, and off the thigh pad fine down the leg side
swings away just before pitching on a good length outside off, left alone, swings away again just before it reaches the keeper
bowled much fuller for the stumps now, Simmons is back and across and pushes to mid on
on the pads, but he calmly tucks the length ball to the leg side
bounce as it is angled across the left-hander, who lets it go
neat, Gayle gets off the mark in uncharacteristic fashion, gets forward and pushes a pitched up ball softly past extra cover
excellent leave, close to off stump, angling away slightly on a length, enough for Gayle to pull the bat away
another leave, this one was easier, the ball slightly doing more with the angle outside off
Mills persisting with the angle across Gayle outside off stump, and the batsman continues to have a look and let them go, can he get one to bend back in, there is not a lot of swing on offer
length ball, tight line on off stump, Simmons pushes it with an open face to off
angled down the leg side, Simmons shuffling across too much outside off stump, and misses the tickle
now he gets the front foot out too far across, and gets hit high on the pad as he misses a climbing length ball, which was going down leg
pushes out towards covers
bowled from wide of the crease, hurled in full, Simmons defends solidly

another failure for Simmons, and New Zealand have struck with one of the new balls, Southee is pumped, nice line, angles it in full just outside off stump, it starts to move away before pitching, Simmons is tentative, ends up shuffling across in the crease, and feathering it to the keeper, as he pushes away from the body, shot of a man in no form
widish and back of a length outside off, moving away and left alone easily
left with the angle across him outside off
and there he goes, he is done with the leaving, this one was slightly closer to off, slightly fuller, in Gayle's zone, and he puts front foot out and clobbers it over the long off boundary
appeal for lbw as he is struck on the left leg, which is high in the air, as he tries the pull to a short of a length ball, was struck just outside the line of off, pretty high too,

well, well, this has been the difference, they need to get this man early, second six for Gayle, Mills tries the slower one, pitched up again, outside off, and Gayle hammers it over wide long off, that just flew and was still travelling as it crashed into the upper tiers of the stand
another one, he did not even move his feet this time, stood in the crease, swung eagerly, and the ball obliged, it disappeared over the long off boundary
the crowd was expecting another one, there is a roar of surprise as Gayle calmly defends this one, bowled shorter than the previous ones, on a good length
backward point slides to his left to stop the ball as Smith pushes away from the body
beaten, again he goes searching for the ball away from the body, it swings away full from just outside off
slightly late on the full delivery, but manages to shuffle across and defend with bat and pad together
full again, pushed softly down the pitch, mid off gets across and fields
appeal for catch down the leg side but it is called a wide, did not look to be bat involved
played out to the leg side
gets forward and pushes with a thick inside edge to square leg, slight turn on off
there is a delay as the umpires check with the third umpire for a caught behind appeal, Gayle looking to punch from the crease, edged it into the ground and into Watling, who managed to hold on
here he comes, skips out, reaches the pitch easily, and lifts it straight down the ground
short and widish now, Gayle happily thumps it in front of point
bounce now, some turn too, Gayle steps out and has to defend it away from the high part of the bat
down the track again, not quite in control, but forces it past midwicket
Southee has Gayle surprised by a very sharp bouncer, he was on the front foot, and had to take evasive action as the ball took off at him, just manages to avoid it
the next one is pitched up, middle stump line, but Gayle manages to work it behind square leg, the straight sixes get all the attention, but he scores a lot of runs in the square leg area
this is serious slaughter, Gayle sees this one bowled full outside off, bends the knee, gets forward and lofts it over extra cover, what have you got, Tim?
Southee bowls it still fuller, close to the blockhole, and Gayle has no trouble in keeping it out
just around the off stump, full length, he gets slightly forward and across and pushes it towards cover
very full from Southee, Gayle mistimes it as he tries to squeeze it away through point
starts with a full delivery which is driven to mid on
width, but punched away straight to point
this should have gone as well, wide again, Smith is not all that confident on the off, though, again he finds a fielder, at cover this time
played out to the man at mid on
too much width again, and finally Smith is able to pick the gap on the off side, punches it between cover and point
back and across and pushes a length ball on the off side
this is seriously two batsmen batting with one bat, one of them leaves as if in a Test match, one of them thumps sixes as if in a T20, the former is switched on for this delivery outside off
defended to short cover
good line, close to off stump, angling away, Gayle gets a thick inside edge to square leg as he pushes at it
again he is tentative to one on off stump, back of a length, gets across and jabs it off an inside edge square on the leg side, there is a ricochet and they will take two more
quietly played out to cover
length, on the pads, worked behind square leg for an easy couple
appeal for lbw, but Smith managed an inside edge to a length ball angled in
full, he shatters the stumps at the non-striker's end with a drive, Oram appeals, possibly for run out, he was a mile away from the ball
gets across and turns it from off stump to mid on, oh yeah, he is leg side oriented alright
worked softly off the pads square for a single
this time he was looking to defend to covers, with a huge forward stride, you can't blame him if ti still goes to mid on
widish outside off stump from a good length, left alone
tight line, on off stump, played with an open face to point
another one played out to point with an open face from the crease
that surprised him, took off from back of a length, Gayle took a hand off the bat as the ball hit close to the splice
a thick edge runs between short third man and backward point as Gayle pushes forward with an angled bat, it is pulled back with a slide but the fielder was touching the rope
plays out a pitched up slower one down the pitch
pushed towards long on for one
well down the pads and tucked behind square leg
walks down the track, Oram bangs it in short, and it moves a long way in and goes down the leg side
there it comes, this is one stroke he owns, shortish from Oram, and Smith winds up to pull it flat over the deep midwicket boundary
Oram goes full now, but Smith is ready, he swings it from just outside off over the bowler, and into the straight boundary
length outside off stump, runs it behind point
back of a length, worked square on leg
rolls away behind square on off as he mistimes a full ball
gets forward and pushes on the off side
flat and angled in quick on off stump, pushed to the bowler
well bowled, angled in full and straightens and bounces to take a thick edge to short third man, the single brings up Gayle's fifth fifty in six matches since his comeback
pushed back to the bowler
almost hit it back to the bowler, full and spinning in, Smith pushes hard, it bounces just short of  McCullum
flighted full on the pads and worked to wide long on past midwicket's dive
full delivery driven down to long off
pushed away off the front foot square on leg
biff, floats it up slightly, only slightly wide outside off, Gayle reaches for it, and the ball disappears into the sightscreen
could that have been a stumping chance, Gayle getting out as he looked to work a tossed up ball, missed it as it spun down leg, Watling missed too, short fine leg fields, need replays
skiddy, and spinning into the pads, whipped to midwicket
angled in, leans forward and turns it off the pads in front of square
punched back to the bowler from the crease
short, spinning in quick, punched to long on

big appeal for lbw turned down, NZ review it, Gayle hit on the pad as he pushes forward, misses a quick length ball that skids in the with the angle from around the stumps, striking him just outside the line of off stump, umpire's call stands, and Gayle lives on
bat in front of pad as he works it from middle and leg to midwicket
too short, too wide, Smith thumps it straight to extra cover
flighted, pushed off the front foot to mid on
quick and full on off stump, leans forward to defend
skidding from short of a length on leg, turned in front of square
tossed up, straightening, Gayle gets forward to block
skidding in on middle and leg, he gets across in the crease and turns it to leg
spins in from back of a length, clipped to the leg side, no feet at all from Smith, he was cramped up by that one
length ball is thumped towards long-off, 'Catch,' is the cry but that reaches the fielder on the bounce
defended from the crease to the right of the bowler
murderous hit from Gayle, that was pitched up and it is absolutely hammered, flat and hard it went, over the bowler's head, long-on doesn't even bother attempting to chase that, he had no chance
defended to the off side this time
stays in the crease and nudges it towards square leg

there's the breakthrough New Zealand were desperately searching for, Dwayne Smith is gone as he looked to play a full delivery towards long-on, a leading edge and that swirls towards long-off, safely taken
full ball pitching on leg stump, punched back towards the bowler
slides that down the leg, cramping up Samuels who had to adjust after taking a big forward stride, defended towards mid-on
wide outside off, Samuels refrains from chasing that
great delivery to finish a maiden wicket, Samuels chases that and is beaten outside off
tucked wide of short fine leg off the pads
too far down the leg side, Gayle tries to get to it, but cannot
length ball, on the pads once again, worked square
angled into middle and leg, fuller length, nudged in front of square
low full toss, leg stump line once again, at least this is preventing the sixes for now, worked through square leg
good line, around off stump, bouncing from a good length, he shuffles across and drops it down, not getting the run
stays beside the line and opens the face to run it behind point
low full toss floated in to the pads, turned past square leg
neatly done, goes back quickly to run a length ball to short third
skips out now to push solidly past extra cover's dive
beaten on the cut, it skids on flat outside off from a length
turns away from leg stump, bounces too, defended from the crease
flat, wide, cut in front of point
width outside off, back of a length, he swivels and controls the pull to deep midwicket
worked in front of square leg off the pads
leans forward, bat and pad together, defended
shuffles across, and adjusts for some extra bounce on this one to punch to point
back of a length outside off, runs it down to third man
they are keeping him to singles with this full line on the pads, tucked in front of square
starts well with a pitched up ball, leg and middle, Gayle leans forward to defend
still fuller, leg stump line, Mills has recovered well from the hammering he took early on, Gayle pushes it back down the pitch
squeezes a full delivery, on middle and off, wide of extra cover for a single
back of a length, angled in, turned in front of square
works a full delivery to midwicket
angled in from wide of the crease, off the pads to fine leg
Southee arrives and continues with the leg stump line to Gayle, who earns another single towards midwicket
steered to third man
off stump line for once to Gayle, dipping full toss, Gayle leans out, and manages a thick edge past the keeper
back of a length, pushed to covers for a sharp run
worked square on the leg side
boom, and he is welcomed first ball with a mammoth straight six, slight room to swing his arms, full just outside off, and that is enough
very full, almost in the blockhole, dug out
pads away a skidding length ball straightening, comfortably missing off stump
on the pads, worked square on the leg side
takes a step out and pushes with the spin to square leg
straightening on off stump, goes across and defends
floated up on the pads, nudged to square leg, he'll have a look first
forced to midwicket from off stump
width as it spins in from outside off, cut straight to short third man
this will beat short third man comfortably, flighted full and quick, Samuels flails at it, and a thick edge races past the keeper
played out to midwicket with the turn
down the track, and eases it past the non-striker, wide of long on
flat one spinning away a bit outside off, slapped to sweeper cover
quick on leg, nudged with the spin to the left of short fine
stays back to a flighted one on leg stump, stabs it close to the pitch
forced it away off the pad square on the leg side
pushed back to the bowler
pitching leg and spinning too wide down the leg side, keeper cannot get to it
another one spin down the leg side, not as wild as the previous one, Watling collects
angled full outside off now, Gayle reaches out and whips it in the air over midwicket
wides coming at both ends from NZ, Nicol sprays it down leg now
gets hold of a flat one outside off, and cuts it through point, sweeper covers gets around to it
gets forward and pushes to extra cover
flat and spinning across, pushed out to extra cover again
played out from middle to the leg side softly
quick and full on middle and leg, bat and pad together as he keeps it out
he won't let Nicol get away with a tight over, sees it pitch full outside off, not much width, but Gayle cranks up, lunges forward, and deposits it over long off
flat and quick, cut hard wide of sweeper cover
onto 98 now, fired in full on off stump, he gets forward and smokes it straight over the bowler
appeal for caught behind turned down, Gayle going reaching out to one angling across him, New Zealand were confident, there did not seem to be an edge, NZ have no reviews left
pushed back to the bowler
worked through square leg
full delivery fired in, driven down to long on
driven wide of extra cover
steps out, and finds extra cover with a push
comes out again, and drives down to long off
full toss worked away to midwicket

this time he will get it, manages to get something on the ball as he forces a full delivery on its way very fine down the leg side, celebrates with a broad smile, this has been a very productive comeback so far, coach Gibson joins in the applause, Gayle waves his bat all around the ground as he soaks in all the applause from his home crowd
driven down to long off
cuts a very wide one down to third man
tossed up on middle and off, defended off the front foot
pushed back to the bowler
superb stroke, Samuels has used his feet well to spin, skips out, reaches the pitch and whips against the turn over midwicket, it is timed so well it carries over the rope, some timing
worked square on the leg side
spinning in from a good length, worked wristily to fine leg
short of length ball just outside off stump, pushed towards backward point
short of length ball on leg stump, clipped behind square leg
short of length and angling in, tucked towards midwicket
shotish and outside off, guided down towards fine leg for a single
length ball on off stump, pushed towards mid-off for a single
length ball just outside off, opens the face and guides the ball behind point

tossed up and another effortless hit, for a while I thought that was a catch, it was only a few yards wide of long-on but that had much too much power for the fielder there, Nethula has his hands on his head
and another, murderous straight hit, doesn't go all the way this time, one-bounce four
pushed off the back foot towards midwicket for a single
inside-edge towards square leg for a single
one of the few times Gayle has missed when he gone for a big hit, instead of his successful tactic of hitting straight, this time he looks to swipe it towards the deep square leg boundary, he misses
leg stump delivery looks to work it away behind square leg, can't connect properly
pitched up and just outside off, punched towards deep extra cover for a couple
tossed this wide outside off, Samuels looks to push it towards cover off the front foot, that drifted away from him and past the outside edge
pushed towards mid-on for a single this time, brings up the 200 in the 34th over
walks through for a single after pushing the ball for a single

too short from McCullum and that is pulled towards deep square leg, the batsmen sprint back for the second, the throw was a few yards too wide of the stumps, a more accurate one and Samuels would have been in trouble
pushed towards extra cover for one more
short of length and just outside off, opens the face to steer it towards short third man
back of length and on middle and off, pushed towards Oram
on the pads this time, nudged towards midwicket for an ambled single
full and on the pads, squeezed out to deep square leg for a quick couple
pitched up and that is punched towards sweeper cover for another sharp two, not something Gayle is accustomed to
Oram keeps it around off, defended to the off side by Samuels
full, slow and on leg stump, squeezed out to midwicket
mishits a very low full toss towards mid on
full on leg once again, worked square
width, and Samuels gets to his fifty, emphatically dispatching it between cover and point
low full toss driven to long off
around the blockhole on middle, squeezed out to extra cover
Gayle was backing away to leg, Oram went that direction as well, but overdid it, and Gayle allowed it to slip past him down the leg side
very full on leg stump, eased down to long on
length ball on the pads worked through square leg
thick inside edge wide of short fine leg as he goes for the cover drive
full outside leg stump, away to deep square leg
too wide and full, but he belts it straight to cover
very full again, not much margin but he has managed it, squeezed out to mid off
another one around the blockhole, Samuels can only dig it towards mid off
low full toss, a straight drive crashes into the non-striker's stumps, and rolls towards mid on

respite, belated, for New Zealand, Gayle has drilled a full toss off his pads straight to deep midwicket, his expression gives nothing away, Samuels walks over to shake his hand, and Gayle walks back with a raised bat to generous applause, what an entertainer
length ball, leaves it alone outside off stump
walks across and whips a length ball with the angle, on the bounce to short fine leg
gets a slow and short ball wide outside off, he is standing outside his crease, tries to reach out and swat it away, cannot get to it
defended off the front foot
excellent stroke, Samuels has looked in fine touch today, gets forward to a pitched up ball outside off and eases it past extra cover, all timing
and again, top stroke, Southee bowls it closer to off stump, full again, Samuels makes some room and opens the face to beat extra cover comfortably

third time, Gayle was all power, Samuels has been timing them superbly, Southee continues to pitch them up, and Samuels continues to put them away, that man at extra cover cannot do anything, the ball goes wider of him this time
angles it into leg stump now, forced towards midwicket
full one worked to deep square leg
Southee ends the over alright, bowls it into the blockhole, Samuels cannot force it away
pitched up, he mistimes a lofted shot down to long on
right into the blockhole, Samuels get the bat down just in time to keep it from hitting off stump
pushed back to the bowler
that was going to be another boundary for Samuels through the covers, wide delivery had been timed well, but extra cover put in the big dive to deny him

that was a run out chance, Pollard dropped a back of a length ball very close to the stumps and towards the keeper, Samuels called him for a single, had Watling hit, Samuels would have been gone by about two feet
drives to long on for one
crack! a length ball has been whipped hard from outside off stump to the deep midwicket boundary
short, looks to pull very hard, but mistimes the stroke, gets a single to leg
full delivery squeezed out to extra cover, Pollard wants the single, Samuels does not, Samuels wins
into the leg stump, around the blockhole, pushed down to long on
that looked gone, Pollard misses a full toss angled in, struck in front of middle and leg, and given right away, however, ball tracker shows us the delivery would have missed leg stump with the angle
fired full down the leg side, he reaches for it and nudges it to short fine
tossed up on leg stump, straightens, pops up as he pushes forward
rocks back to a legbreak just outside off and punches to sweeper cover
flighted once again, middle and leg, I like this legspinner, pushed off the front foot to the off side
steered to short third man
tries to run a spinning legbreak to third man but is beaten
back of a length, and kicks from there, rolls away off glove to the leg side
right into the blockhole from Oram, middle stump line, jammed away to the off side
beats short third man's dive, Nethula there, could have stopped it, Samuels opening the face as he drove at a low and wide full toss
another four, thick outside edge as Samuels gets forward, it runs past the keeper
full toss outside off, away to third man
hit past the bowler to long on
back of the hand slower one, pushed to extra cover for a single
squeezed out to long off for a single
low full toss on middle and leg, down to long on

gone, New Zealand have not done badly in these end overs, Southee sends another yorker for Bravo's legs, he cannot get them out of the way, pings the boot and crashes into the off stump, Southee appealed initially before realising he did not need to, Bravo limps off in some pain
drives a full ball outside off to extra cover, who dives to keep them to one
first ball, captain Sammy goes straight down the ground, with a very straight bat
slapped away through point
wide and flat, cut away for one
backs away and thumps a flat legspinner to long off
beaten, bounce from a length on off stump, turn as well, past the outside edge as he pushes forward
short, spinning in, he forces the pull in the air, falls short of deep midwicket running to his right
driven to extra cover
excellent placement, short again, Sammy rocks back and punches it over midwicket, it is not a pull, but has power alright
quick and full delivery squeezed back to the bowler
drills down a full ball to long on
around the blockhole, squeezed out to the off side
full delivery driven down to long on
in the blockhole once again, he gets the front leg out of the way and jams it away through midwicket
pitched up, drives it down the ground
full outside off, whips it off a thick inside edge to short fine leg
not a bad over at all from Southee, full again around the blockhole, pushed straight back to the bowler
full, dragged from outside off stump to long on
back and across, nudges a length ball to leg, and gets the single
charges out, Oram digs it in short, Sammy swivels and manages to awkwardly pull it away
Samuels is getting the singles he requires, shuffles across and drops a length ball towards point
too short, too wide, Sammy waits, reaches out for it, and gives the cut a full swing of the bat, carries all the way into the deep backward point rope
Sammy retains strike, jamming one in the blockhole down to long on
hits a full delivery on middle to long on
New Zealand have been mostly around the blockhole at the death, Sammy makes some room and digs it out to long on
onto 98 now with a soft push off a full delivery to covers
third time today a stroke has hit the non-striker's stumps, ricochets away to the leg side
gets a full toss, but cannot hit it wide enough of long on , gets only a single
there is the third ODI hundred for Marlon Samuels with a single to third man, his last one was in December 2006, Samuels jumps and punches the air with emotion, Gayle applauds in the dressing room
in the blockhole, just outside off, Sammy misses
one more yorker, on the stumps now from wide of the crease, Sammy jabs it away to the keeper, they cannot get the single
can't get it away again, Oram fires another one in full, on to leg stump, Sammy tries to whip it over midwicket, ball rolls away to the off side
yet another full one, can't get it farther than point
Oram ends on target, full length, Sammy swings hard straight to long off

inn2.comm: plays out a whippy length delivery to the off side
back and across to a 133 kph back of a length ball and blocks
hitting the bat hard from an eager run-up, Nicol pushes at it and gets it down to third man
that was quick and took off, 137 kph bouncer, went just over Guptill's shoulder
was looking to leave it initially, then started to bring a defensive bat down, the back of a length ball beat the inside edge in the end
well forward to smother a pitched up delivery around off
bustles in and sends it down the leg side from a good length
pushes forward and defends to covers
drives, out to extra cover, Pollard puts in an awkward dive and saves runs
length ball pushed out to backward point now
awkwardly stabs it down to third man, he was coming forward and across and the short of a length ball bounced at him
gets bat in front of pad and pushes it away to midwicket
moves away sharply after passing the batsman outside off
gets behind the line of a back of a length ball on off to block
they will need to do this throughout the innings, down the track, and whips away a length ball past short fine leg
nice, rides the bounce on a short of a length ball and drops it softly in front of point
short at 131 kph, pulled away to deep square leg
wide, but he mistimes the stroke as he looks to put it away through point
slower, at 124 kph, that is why it did not come on well, he pushes it away tentatively to extra cover
fine leave, straight length ball not far from off, then moves away when it nears the keeper
tries to clobber a length ball over the bowler, but misses as it holds its line
pushes forward, and is surprised by some extra bounce off a length, away to third man
beaten, 137 kph back of a length ball moving away, he goes after it but cannot connect
now Nicol tries to skip out and go down the ground, the length ball straightens and he is beaten totally
worked behind square leg
they have decided stepping out is the way to go, gets out, and crouches to lift a low full toss over midwicket
Smith at backward point saves four with a dive to his left, Nicol had powered the cut away
defended with a shuffle across to off
again steps out, Russell goes short, mishits a pull through square leg
gets across and defends a pitched up ball angled in, down the pitch
shot, full, into the pads, and he whips it powerfully to the right of mid on
swats a back of a length ball wide of midwicket
holds its line from a length on off, worked square on leg
not sure how long this approach is going to work, he stepped out and crashed a length ball, but straight to mid off
swatted to midwicket for one
shuffles across and works it off pad square on leg

the third swat he has played this over, and this time he picks out short midwicket, who had just moved in, Rampaul digging it back of a length again, and smiling and pointing knowingly towards Gayle after the catch was taken
pitched up now, around off, pushed to the bowler
gets forward and defends a length ball
that was too short, wide, and Guptill swivels to crack a pull over midwicket
pushes forward, brings bat around pad and works to midwicket
beaten first ball by a length delivery angled across outside off, pushes the bat outside the line, and is late on it as well
shuffles across and punches, gets it down to third man
angles it in to middle and leg, eased down to mid on
confusion, whips a shortish one through square leg, Guptill runs halfway up the pitch for the second, Smith keeps them to one eventually
to short third man for one
short, leg stump line, and is pulled away behind square leg
defends a length ball on the stumps to the leg side
pushes a length ball outside off to short extra cover
goes after a pitched up ball going across him, and the thick edge flies past the lone slip
width, and he crashes it behind point, who took pace off it with a dive for short third man to run around and save the boundary
gets across and pushes a length ball to mid off
short of length ball just outside off, defended that towards point
length ball outside off, punched towards cover from the crease
length and once more in the channel outside off, blocked towards cover off the front foot, that was 136kph from Rampaul
after starting the over with three deliveries probing around the off stump, Rampaul sprays one on the pads, helped along to fine leg for four
reverts to the off stump line again, and that is another dot ball as Guptill defends

a touch shorter, and just a bit of width, and that is a lovely stroke from Guptill, stayed on the back foot and drove that through cover, an on-the-up drive for four, not much wrong with that delivery from Rampaul
length ball outside off is nudged towards midwicket
pitched up and outside off, guided towards backward point by Guptill
on the pads, mild lbw appeal, helped down to fine leg for a single
length and on off stump, blocked towards cover
back of a length, on middle and off, poked towards cover
oh, Flynn survives, he had earlier edged one to the left of the wide slip, this time he nicks it to the right of Gayle at slip, picks up another boundary as well, Flynn living dangerously
spins in from a length towards off, tucked towards midwicket
spins a long way away outside off, left alone
again big spin for Narine, Flynn plays inside the line of that one
third man proving very productive for Flynn here, this wasn't an edge, it was a controlled glide past slip for four to third man

this is another edge, this isn't running away to the third man boundary, this has been taken low to his right by Bravo at slip, Narine strikes in his first over, he's finding international cricket at home easy indeed
spins a long way, there's some bounce as well, the turn however takes the ball down the leg side, runs away for five wides
Williamson looks to tuck that towards the leg side, a leading edge towards point
short of length ball outside off, played with soft hands towards backward point, Guptill thinks about a single but decides against it
defended to the off side off the front foot
short of length ball is punched off the back foot towards point for a single
similar length, a touch wider this time, Williamson rocks on to the back foot and slaps that towards deep point for a couple
slightly fuller, again some width on offer, punched towards extra cover off the front foot
slower  ball, 108kph, full and just outside off, worked towards wide mid-on to end the over
the menacing Narine begins the next over with a tossed up delivery on off stump, defended
fuller and on middle, nudged off the back foot towards midwicket
'catch it,' is the shout after the ball is worked towards square leg, was in the air for a bit but lands well short
slapped off the back foot towards cover
heading for the pads, defended to the leg side
once more a leading edge once more for Williamson, he was again trying to work it to the leg side, the ball pops up to the off side
Sammy's first ball is nudged behind square leg
short of length and well outside off, punched towards cover
helped towards midwicket for one more
pushed towards extra cover by Guptill
slanting in towards the pads, helped down to fine leg for a single

this one goes straight one, it was flatter and pitching on off stump, blocked off the back foot
pitched up, on middle and leg, worked past mid-on for a single
another one which goes straight, more defence, but Narine has overstepped
makes the most of the free-hit, jumps away from leg stump, overpitched ball is clobbered inside-out over extra cover for six
on the pads, this is worked behind square leg for a single to end the over
short of length ball outside off, nothing happening here for Sammy, pretty much going straight on, that was tapped towards cover
length ball on off stump, guided down to third man for an easy single

great effort from Simmons at cover, he moved to his right and then leapt up, managed to get his right hand on it but couldn't latch on to the ball, it was a slower on from Sammy, a full toss outside off, which was hit towards cover by the batsman who was surprised by the lack of pace
short of length and way outside off, 127kph, stabbed towards point, they really should be looking to score more off Sammy, there is little in this pitch for him
a mild lbw appeal from Sammy, that was off the bat and onto the pad, and was also unlikely to be hitting the stumps, too high and possibly hitting outside off as well
tossed up full offspinner eased to long on
full ball pushed off the front foot to covers

on the front foot to a straighter one and pushed to mid off
angled full on the pads and turned wide of midwicket

worked in front of square leg
full, on the stumps, Guptill lifts it over the bowler neatly

pushes a full delivery to the man at long on

punched to mid off
on the front foot and pushes to mid off again
forced to extra cover this time

back of a length, pushed to extra cover
width, crashed out to sweeper cover, just a single

a whip wide of midwicket for a single
bounce from outside off as he bowls an offspinner from wide of the crease, pushed back

quicker, fuller, and he crouches to steer it past short third man

that could have been tight, KW pulling a short ball high in the air off the front foot, falls over Pollard running back from midwicket
punched to sweeper cover
worked wide of deep midwicket, the throw is very wild
full delivery into the stumps turned to midwicket

swats a flat offspinner to long on
backs away and punches against the turn to sweeper cover
leans forward and pushes out to midwicket
the asking rate is now above eight an over as he is beaten outside off stump
that is it, Guptill is gone, soft dismissal, pushing a full and quick delivery straight back at Samuels who accepts it happily
leans forward and across and pushes to cover
pushed to mid off for one
back of a length, outside off, guided straight to point, and the throw arrives to send the non-striker back to his crease
length ball turned wide of mid on for a single

straight to midwicket, and Samuels gets his second wicket, Latham shuffling across, going deep in the crease and punching in the air, Charles the substitue fielder dives to his right and plucks a low catch
moving across to outside off stump and working it in front of square leg
fine pull to a short ball from some way outside off stump, wide of deep square leg

back of a length, he heaves it down to deep midwicket

offspinner turning in on off and middle, worked square on leg

played out to point
full delivery, cracked wide of sweeper cover, who fumbles the pick-up

touch slower, he is beaten on the outside edge as he comes forward
wide down the leg side, helped down to fine leg

punched down to long on for one

nice, but these have been rare to come, KW gets forward and lofts a pitched up ball cleanly over mid off

spins in, steered to short third man from the crease
been that kind of innings, full toss hit straight to extra cover

wide and slapped wide of sweeper cover, they think about the second, but decide not to take on Smith's throw, it is wide in the end
Sammy going for runs this over, full toss turned past short fine leg now
full, eased down with the spin to long on

drags the pull behind square leg now for a couple, runs coming rather freely now
pitched up around off stump, pushed to long on

wide, very wide outside off stump, he cannot reach out to it

turned to deep midwicket with the angle
short of a length, pulled to deep midwicket
clipped in the air down to deep midwicket
fired in full and goes down the leg side as he misses the paddle
94 kph full delivery turned to midwicket
full toss forced through cover, needs a big slide to pull it back in
takes it almost from off stump as he backs away and dabs it to short third man
cut to short third man again
pulled to deep midwicket
some inswing, length ball into middle and leg, dropped on to the on side
again some inward movement, full outside off stump, through to the keeper as he misses
heaved wide of long on from off, fielder cannot prevent the second run
fine shot, picked it up very well, swinging in full on off and middle, and lifted over midwicket
tries to lift the free hit again, finer this time, but cannot connect

that's gone for six, Watling bends forward, gets on a knee, and scoops a low full toss all the way for six over short fine leg, unbelievable, these scoops
squeezed out towards point
angled in full on the pads, turned through midwicket
worked through square leg, who fails to stop the ball, Sammy it is

beaten on the cut with a straighter one
carrom ball pushed out to point from a good length
worked from leg stump in front of square

widish, driven off the front foot to point
turned through square leg

comes out and pushes to sweeper cover
he was looking to reverse sweep, the ball was floated full and well down leg, then he tried to sweep but missed, not given a wide

low full toss crunched to sweeper cover
length ball on the pads worked through square leg
beaten on the drive as he goes for a pitched up ball outside off

behind square leg for a single
